  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To call it hospital would be a little exaggeration.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I would call it maximally hospice.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was the same block as the others-- the only thing is the front was converted.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In the front, there was a-- the bedroom of the head of the hospital compound and the block.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And on the other side, there was some kind of a [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] space, which could be an office with a table-- office table.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then, attached to it was a room where there was an operating table-- something like an operating room.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Across from it was a small room, which was a magazine for supplies-- mostly the bread which was brought in, was kept for about two or three days.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then there was a very primitive type of pharmacy, where two prison pharmacists were preparing whatever-- I mean, we brought sometimes from the incoming transport, so that sometimes we had some medicaments, which were left to us.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Also, they were preparing special stuff.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "A tablet was put together, simply a kind of a container out of edible type of material, and the powder was put into it-- as more primitive kind of capsules were done that way.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "What was the medication which was to our disposal was very primitive.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Sometimes we got sulfa drugs, which was unusual.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we had aspirin, or acetaminophen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that would be about the extent of it-- or exceptional when they wanted or brought something unusual, like when they probably spread some kind of a disease through the camp.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "For sometimes, part of the block-- one has to imagine that you have got about, on each side, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] 15 rows of triple bunks, on which there were sick persons, the sick prisoners lying.",
      "word_count": 37
    }
  ],
